<div class="recepies-page">
    <div class="upper">
        <img src="/paella3.jpg" alt="Paella2" width="400" height="350">  
        <h3>Seafood Paella</h3>
    </div>
    <div class="list">
        <h3>Ingredients: </h3>
        <% for(let i=0; i<ingredient.length; i++) { %>
           <% for(let j=0; j<ingredient[i].paella.length;j++) { %>
            <input class="check" type="checkbox" id="aliment_<%=i%>">
            <label for="aliment_<%=i%>"><%=ingredient[i].paella[j]%></label><br/>
        <%}
        } %>
    </div>
    <div class="steps">
        <h3>Steps: </h3>
        <ol start="1">
            <li>In a large paella pan heat the olive oil over medium heat. Add the chicken and sausage, 
                season with salt and pepper, then cook for about 5 minutes until the chicken is no longer pink.
            </li>
            <li>Move the chicken and sausage to one side of the pan, then add onion to the other half, season with a bit of 
                salt and pepper and cook for 2 minutes until the onion becomes translucent and soft. Add the garlic 
                and cook for another minute.
            </li>
            <li>Add the arborio and fire roasted tomatoes to the pan and stir well. 
                Let the rice cook in the sauce from the tomatoes for about 5 minutes, you will notice it will start to 
                brown on the bottom, which is what you're looking for. Add the broth, hot sauce, smoked paprika, saffron and season with salt and pepper 
                if needed. Stir everything together and cover with a large lid. Cook for about 15 minutes or until most of the liquid has 
                been absorbed by the rice. The rice will not me cooked trough at this time.
            </li>
            <li>Turn down the heat and stir the rice around a bit, you will notice the crust on the bottom of the pan, that's 
                what we are looking for. Arrange the shrimp, mussels and clams over the rice, cover with a lid again and cook 
                for another 10 minutes or until the mussels and clams open up.
            </li>
            <li>Turn off the heat and garnish with parsley and lemon wedges.
            </li>
        </ol><br/><br/>
    </div>
    <div class="ajax">
        <button class="show" id="ajax-button">Press for Link to Video</button>
        <script
            src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.5.1.min.js"
            integrity="sha256-9/aliU8dGd2tb6OSsuzixeV4y/faTqgFtohetphbbj0="
            crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
        <script>
            $(function(){
                $("#ajax-button").click( function(){
                    $.ajax({
                        async: true,
                        url: '/ajax.json',
                        dataType: 'json',
                        type: 'GET',
                        success: function(data){
                            $('#show-ajax').html("<a href="+data[0].videos[6]+">"+data[0].videos[6]+"</a>")
                            console.log(data[0].videos[0]);
                        }, 
                        error: function(e){
                            console.log(e);
                        }
                    })
                })
            })
        </script>
        <div id="show-ajax"></div>
    </div>
    <%if (locals.user){ %>
        <div class="comments">
            <form action="comentarii" method="post">
                <input type="hidden" name="page_name" value="paella">
                <label for="comentariu">Review: </label>
                <textarea id="comentariu" name="comentariu" rows="4" cols="55"> </textarea>
                <br/><br/>
                <input id="button-log" type="submit" value="Add comment">    
            </form>
        </div>
    <%} %>
</div>